  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for dpdk",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for dpdk fixes the following issues:\n\nSecurity:\n- CVE-2021-3839: Fixed a memory corruption issue during vhost-user communication\n  (bsc#1198963).\n- CVE-2022-0669: Fixed a denial of service that could be triggered by a vhost-user\n  master (bsc#1198964).\n\nBugfixes:\n- kni: allow configuring thread granularity (bsc#1195172).\n- Fixed reading of PCI device name as UTF strings (bsc#1198873).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
